epared, and that many of the stranded vehicles were not suitable for driving in the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">extreme weather </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">conditions. There were also concerns about p</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">oor driving and lack of experience/skills for the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">road </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">conditions. There were a large number of comments about the number of potholes in all types of road, and the observation that they are particularly dangerous when it has snowed, because they cannot be </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">seen.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">”</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">GENERAL RESILIENCE OF THE ROAD NETWORK</span></p><p style="margin:11.25pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">RAC believes that the ability of the Highways Agency and local authorities to respond to adverse weather and keep the roads operation</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">al in the most extreme weather </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">has improved since </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">2009/10. The recommendatio</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ns of the Quarmby report have generally been implemented and </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">have delivered the </span><span style="fon